// An Ok result wraps a runtime-built (non-interned) heap string. The result
// object itself is kept alive by the local `r`, but the wrapped string is
// reachable only through ObjResult::mark walking `self.value`.
//
// After collection we build fresh strings so that, if the inner value were
// wrongly freed, its slot would be reused and `r.unwrap()` would read back
// garbage instead of "foo".

say r = Ok("fo" + "o");
gcCollect();

say pad1 = "aa" + "bb";
say pad2 = "cc" + "dd";
say pad3 = "ee" + "ff";

print(r.unwrap()); // expect: foo
